Job.Description:
Collaborated within an Agile Squad of 5 members for the development of the "Santé des Armées" application as part of a project to create a digital healthcare platform exclusively for the French Army;
Responsible for setting up Build and Run operations using Spring Boot 2 (Java 11) and Angular 9 to ensure a robust and scalable architecture;
Implemented unit and integration tests using JUnit 5 and Mockito 5 to ensure code quality, contributing to a significant increase in test coverage for the application;
Actively contributed to continuous integration and deployment with Gitlab CI, Kubernetes, and Ansible on a private cloud, facilitating rapid and reliable application delivery;
Close coordination of efforts within the team, especially with functional leads and project managers, through daily and weekly meetings to ensure project deadlines and budgets are met;
Adopted agile methodology to optimize team efficiency, reduce delays, improve code quality, and ensure regular delivery, increased application stability, and high user satisfaction;
Implemented advanced authentication mechanisms, including the use of PKI cards for secure user identification and access to sensitive medical data.

Worked independently on the development of a full-stack application for managing the accounting calendar and client portfolio;
Used Node.js 14 and React 17 for development, as well as Shell Scripting for deployment;
Implemented security measures to protect accounting and client portfolio data, including the application of security protocols (HTTPS) and management of security headers.

Contributed to the maintenance of a logistics control application for goods;
Implemented alert and notification systems for potential delays, stockouts, or other logistics issues;
Used technologies such as Express 4, React 16, and MongoDB to ensure smooth operations and an optimal user experience;
Contributed to the implementation of security measures, including protection of cargo tracking data and access rights management to ensure data integrity.

Participated in the development of a digital space for students;
Used the C# 3.1 and ASP.NET 4 stack for the backend, HTML and CSS for the frontend, and SQL Server for the database;
Responsible for implementing a session-based authentication system to ensure secure access to application features;
Played a key role in creating web services and integrating APIs to enhance the user experience.
